  16. ‌type machtype_component =
  17.   | Val
  18.   | Addr
  19.   | Int
  20.   | Float

  22. ‌type machtype = machtype_component array

  24. ‌let typ_void = ([||] : machtype_component array)
  25. ‌let typ_val = [|Val|]
  26. ‌let typ_addr = [|Addr|]
  27. ‌let typ_int = [|Int|]
  28. ‌let typ_float = [|Float|]

  30. (** [machtype_component]s are partially ordered as follows:

  32.       Addr     Float
  33.        ^
  34.        |
  35.       Val
  36.        ^
  37.        |
  38.       Int

  40.   In particular, [Addr] must be above [Val], to ensure that if there is
  41.   a join point between a code path yielding [Addr] and one yielding [Val]
  42.   then the result is treated as a derived pointer into the heap (i.e. [Addr]).
  43.   (Such a result may not be live across any call site or a fatal compiler
  44.   error will result.)
  45. *)

  47. ‌let lub_component comp1 comp2 =
  48.   match comp1, comp2 with
  49.   | Int, Int -> Int
  50.   | Int, Val -> Val
  51.   | Int, Addr -> Addr
  52.   | Val, Int -> Val
  53.   | Val, Val -> Val
  54.   | Val, Addr -> Addr
  55.   | Addr, Int -> Addr
  56.   | Addr, Addr -> Addr
  57.   | Addr, Val -> Addr
  58.   | Float, Float -> Float
  59.   | (Int | Addr | Val), Float
  60.   | Float, (Int | Addr | Val) ->
  61.     (* Float unboxing code must be sure to avoid this case. *)
  62.     assert false

  64. ‌let ge_component comp1 comp2 =
  65.   match comp1, comp2 with
  66.   | Int, Int -> true
  67.   | Int, Addr -> false
  68.   | Int, Val -> false
  69.   | Val, Int -> true
  70.   | Val, Val -> true
  71.   | Val, Addr -> false
  72.   | Addr, Int -> true
  73.   | Addr, Addr -> true
  74.   | Addr, Val -> true
  75.   | Float, Float -> true
  76.   | (Int | Addr | Val), Float
  77.   | Float, (Int | Addr | Val) ->
  78.     assert false

  116. ‌let set_label l =

  238. ‌let iter_shallow_tail f = function
  239.   | Clet(_, _, body) | Cphantom_let (_, _, body) | Clet_mut(_, _, _, body) ->
  240.       f body;
  241.       true
  242.   | Cifthenelse(_cond, _ifso_dbg, ifso, _ifnot_dbg, ifnot, _dbg) ->
  243.       f ifso;
  244.       f ifnot;
  245.       true
  246.   | Csequence(_e1, e2) ->
  247.       f e2;
  248.       true
  249.   | Cswitch(_e, _tbl, el, _dbg') ->
  250.       Array.iter (fun (e, _dbg) -> f e) el;
  251.       true
  252.   | Ccatch(_rec_flag, handlers, body) ->
  253.       List.iter (fun (_, _, h, _dbg) -> f h) handlers;
  254.       f body;
  255.       true
  256.   | Ctrywith(e1, _id, e2, _dbg) ->
  257.       f e1;
  258.       f e2;
  259.       true
  260.   | Cexit _ | Cop (Craise _, _, _) ->
  261.       true
  262.   | Cconst_int _
  263.   | Cconst_natint _
  264.   | Cconst_float _
  265.   | Cconst_symbol _
  266.   | Cvar _
  267.   | Cassign _
  268.   | Ctuple _
  269.   | Cop _ ->
  270.       false

  272. ‌let rec map_tail f = function
  273.   | Clet(id, exp, body) ->
  274.       Clet(id, exp, map_tail f body)
  275.   | Clet_mut(id, kind, exp, body) ->
  276.       Clet_mut(id, kind, exp, map_tail f body)
  277.   | Cphantom_let(id, exp, body) ->
  278.       Cphantom_let (id, exp, map_tail f body)
  279.   | Cifthenelse(cond, ifso_dbg, ifso, ifnot_dbg, ifnot, dbg) ->
  280.       Cifthenelse
  281.         (
  282.           cond,
  283.           ifso_dbg, map_tail f ifso,
  284.           ifnot_dbg, map_tail f ifnot,
  285.           dbg
  286.         )
  287.   | Csequence(e1, e2) ->
  288.       Csequence(e1, map_tail f e2)
  289.   | Cswitch(e, tbl, el, dbg') ->
  290.       Cswitch(e, tbl, Array.map (fun (e, dbg) -> map_tail f e, dbg) el, dbg')
  291.   | Ccatch(rec_flag, handlers, body) ->
  292.       let map_h (n, ids, handler, dbg) = (n, ids, map_tail f handler, dbg) in
  293.       Ccatch(rec_flag, List.map map_h handlers, map_tail f body)
  294.   | Ctrywith(e1, id, e2, dbg) ->
  295.       Ctrywith(map_tail f e1, id, map_tail f e2, dbg)
  296.   | Cexit _ | Cop (Craise _, _, _) as cmm ->
  297.       cmm
  298.   | Cconst_int _
  299.   | Cconst_natint _
  300.   | Cconst_float _
  301.   | Cconst_symbol _
  302.   | Cvar _
  303.   | Cassign _
  304.   | Ctuple _
  305.   | Cop _ as c ->
  306.       f c

  308. ‌let map_shallow f = function
  309.   | Clet (id, e1, e2) ->
  310.       Clet (id, f e1, f e2)
  311.   | Clet_mut (id, kind, e1, e2) ->
  312.       Clet_mut (id, kind, f e1, f e2)
  313.   | Cphantom_let (id, de, e) ->
  314.       Cphantom_let (id, de, f e)
  315.   | Cassign (id, e) ->
  316.       Cassign (id, f e)
  317.   | Ctuple el ->
  318.       Ctuple (List.map f el)
  319.   | Cop (op, el, dbg) ->
  320.       Cop (op, List.map f el, dbg)
  321.   | Csequence (e1, e2) ->
  322.       Csequence (f e1, f e2)
  323.   | Cifthenelse(cond, ifso_dbg, ifso, ifnot_dbg, ifnot, dbg) ->
  324.       Cifthenelse(f cond, ifso_dbg, f ifso, ifnot_dbg, f ifnot, dbg)
  325.   | Cswitch (e, ia, ea, dbg) ->
  326.       Cswitch (e, ia, Array.map (fun (e, dbg) -> f e, dbg) ea, dbg)
  327.   | Ccatch (rf, hl, body) ->
  328.       let map_h (n, ids, handler, dbg) = (n, ids, f handler, dbg) in
  329.       Ccatch (rf, List.map map_h hl, f body)
  330.   | Cexit (n, el) ->
  331.       Cexit (n, List.map f el)
  332.   | Ctrywith (e1, id, e2, dbg) ->
  333.       Ctrywith (f e1, id, f e2, dbg)
  334.   | Cconst_int _
  335.   | Cconst_natint _
  336.   | Cconst_float _
  337.   | Cconst_symbol _
  338.   | Cvar _
  339.     as c ->
  340.       c
